==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clearer
<hw>Clear"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, clears.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gold is a wonderful <qex>clearer</qex> of the understanding.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A tool of which the hemp for
lines and twines, used by sailmakers, is finished.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>clear-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
